{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GyfAkhJd3sswweCb4DsbfW","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've reviewed these initial key files to give you a sense of the project structure. Would you like me to:\n1. Continue reading more source files in the main application packages?\n2. Switch to reading configuration files like persistence.xml or beans.xml?\n3. Read the test files?\n4. Do something else?\n\nThe project appears to be a cargo tracking application built with Jakarta EE and Quarkus, using domain-driven design principles. It has services for booking cargo, tracking handling events, and inspecting cargo routes. The application uses Jakarta validation annotations and seems to have a clean, interface-based architecture.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any aspect of what I've found so far?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9dd45e7-15fd-4879-bcb7-e7ebc835a938","uuid":"2823c5e2-fbaa-4d1f-9601-ca2c5f429dc2"}
