{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018x6w7sEURHtT1QLze7M4wF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n     6→\n     7→/**\n     8→ * This interface provides a way to let other parts of the system know about events that have\n     9→ * occurred.\n    10→ *\n    11→ * <p>It may be implemented synchronously or asynchronously, using for example JMS.\n    12→ */\n    13→public interface ApplicationEvents {\n    14→\n    15→  void cargoWasHandled(HandlingEvent event);\n    16→\n    17→  void cargoWasMisdirected(Cargo cargo);\n    18→\n    19→  void cargoHasArrived(Cargo cargo);\n    20→\n    21→  void receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt);\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SysReiXaKLo3SLnKUXjVfA","session_id":"c9dd45e7-15fd-4879-bcb7-e7ebc835a938","uuid":"7bf50f38-0782-4fc6-9430-173c12acaf68"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MpgVZQK6H7iDKzDHCKHpqX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Future;\n     7→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    11→\n    12→/** Cargo booking service. */\n    13→public interface BookingService {\n    14→\n    15→    /** Registers a new cargo in the tracking system, not yet routed. */\n    16→    TrackingId bookNewCargo(\n    17→            @NotNull(message = \"Origin is required.\") @Valid UnLocode origin,\n    18→            @NotNull(message = \"Destination is required.\") @Valid UnLocode destination,\n    19→            @NotNull(message = \"Deadline is required.\") @Future(\n    20→                    message = \"Deadline must be in the future.\") LocalDate arrivalDeadline);\n    21→\n    22→    /**\n    23→     * Requests a list of itineraries describing possible routes for this cargo.\n    24→     *\n    25→     * @param trackingId Cargo tracking ID\n    26→     * @return A list of possible itineraries for this cargo\n    27→     */\n    28→    List<Itinerary> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(\n    29→            @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId);\n    30→\n    31→    void assignCargoToRoute(\n    32→            @NotNull(message = \"Itinerary is required.\") @Valid Itinerary itinerary,\n    33→            @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId);\n    34→\n    35→    void changeDestination(\n    36→            @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId,\n    37→            @NotNull(message = \"Destination is required.\") @Valid UnLocode unLocode);\n    38→\n    39→    void changeDeadline(\n    40→            @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId,\n    41→            @NotNull(message = \"Deadline is required.\") @Future(\n    42→                    message = \"Deadline must be in the future.\") LocalDate deadline);\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SysReiXaKLo3SLnKUXjVfA","session_id":"c9dd45e7-15fd-4879-bcb7-e7ebc835a938","uuid":"d21963fc-3adf-4e2e-aa6a-31f4ae485aca"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AFePe56r56bRVneDseRNtH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     6→\n     7→public interface CargoInspectionService {\n     8→\n     9→  /**\n    10→   * Inspect cargo and send relevant notifications to interested parties, for example if a cargo has\n    11→   * been misdirected, or unloaded at the final destination.\n    12→   */\n    13→  public void inspectCargo(\n    14→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId);\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SysReiXaKLo3SLnKUXjVfA","session_id":"c9dd45e7-15fd-4879-bcb7-e7ebc835a938","uuid":"0f9dc822-fed4-4cc7-8bad-c41067b81f2a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016heTHYnPjzyM3RS3NYrxff","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    11→\n    12→public interface HandlingEventService {\n    13→\n    14→  /**\n    15→   * Registers a handling event in the system, and notifies interested parties that a cargo has been\n    16→   * handled.\n    17→   */\n    18→  void registerHandlingEvent(\n    19→      @NotNull(message = \"Completion time is required.\") LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    20→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId,\n    21→      @Valid VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    22→      @NotNull(message = \"Location is required.\") @Valid UnLocode unLocode,\n    23→      @NotNull(message = \"Type is required.\") HandlingEvent.Type type)\n    24→      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SysReiXaKLo3SLnKUXjVfA","session_id":"c9dd45e7-15fd-4879-bcb7-e7ebc835a938","uuid":"40a2eb4d-9235-4bc7-8ab5-a848209a81fe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DP5hgX2JzFTxsQbECMUHPB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.Collections;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     7→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    10→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.BookingService;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service.RoutingService;\n    21→\n    22→@ApplicationScoped\n    23→@Transactional\n    24→public class DefaultBookingService implements BookingService {\n    25→\n    26→  @Inject\n    27→  private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    28→  @Inject\n    29→  private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    30→  @Inject\n    31→  private RoutingService routingService;\n    32→  @Inject\n    33→  private Logger logger;\n    34→\n    35→  @Override\n    36→  public TrackingId bookNewCargo(\n    37→      UnLocode originUnLocode, UnLocode destinationUnLocode, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    38→    TrackingId trackingId = cargoRepository.nextTrackingId();\n    39→    Location origin = locationRepository.find(originUnLocode);\n    40→    Location destination = locationRepository.find(destinationUnLocode);\n    41→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    42→        new RouteSpecification(origin, destination, arrivalDeadline);\n    43→\n    44→    Cargo cargo = new Cargo(trackingId, routeSpecification);\n    45→\n    46→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    47→    logger.log(\n    48→        Level.INFO, \"Booked new cargo with tracking ID {0}\", cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString());\n    49→\n    50→    return cargo.getTrackingId();\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  @Override\n    54→  public List<Itinerary> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(TrackingId trackingId) {\n    55→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    56→\n    57→    if (cargo == null) {\n    58→      return Collections.emptyList();\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    return routingService.fetchRoutesForSpecification(cargo.getRouteSpecification());\n    62→  }\n    63→\n    64→  @Override\n    65→  public void assignCargoToRoute(Itinerary itinerary, TrackingId trackingId) {\n    66→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    67→\n    68→    cargo.assignToRoute(itinerary);\n    69→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    70→\n    71→    logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Assigned cargo {0} to new route\", trackingId);\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  @Override\n    75→  public void changeDestination(TrackingId trackingId, UnLocode unLocode) {\n    76→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    77→    Location newDestination = locationRepository.find(unLocode);\n    78→\n    79→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    80→        new RouteSpecification(\n    81→            cargo.getOrigin(), newDestination, cargo.getRouteSpecification().getArrivalDeadline());\n    82→    cargo.specifyNewRoute(routeSpecification);\n    83→\n    84→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    85→\n    86→    logger.log(\n    87→        Level.INFO,\n    88→        \"Changed destination for cargo {0} to {1}\",\n    89→        new Object[] {trackingId, routeSpecification.getDestination()});\n    90→  }\n    91→\n    92→  @Override\n    93→  public void changeDeadline(TrackingId trackingId, LocalDate newDeadline) {\n    94→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    95→\n    96→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    97→        new RouteSpecification(\n    98→            cargo.getOrigin(), cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination(), newDeadline);\n    99→    cargo.specifyNewRoute(routeSpecification);\n   100→\n   101→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n   102→\n   103→    logger.log(\n   104→        Level.INFO,\n   105→        \"Changed deadline for cargo {0} to {1}\",\n   106→        new Object[] {trackingId, newDeadline});\n   107→  }\n   108→}\n   109→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SysReiXaKLo3SLnKUXjVfA","session_id":"c9dd45e7-15fd-4879-bcb7-e7ebc835a938","uuid":"7e79cb94-528b-462b-9382-7592a2497765"}
