{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NMb1ZCAtTtiTYmksMau1U5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→\n     6→/** Jakarta REST configuration. */\n     7→@ApplicationPath(\"rest\")\n     8→public class RestConfiguration extends Application {\n     9→}\n    10→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SysReiXaKLo3SLnKUXjVfA","session_id":"c9dd45e7-15fd-4879-bcb7-e7ebc835a938","uuid":"c0fbf5f3-860c-460d-b0a2-77b5becbb41b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bsts8BiPrNp6YhCPJb4CqQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.logging;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.spi.InjectionPoint;\n     8→\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class LoggerProducer implements Serializable {\n    11→\n    12→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    13→\n    14→  @Produces\n    15→  public Logger produceLogger(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n    16→    String loggerName = extractLoggerName(injectionPoint);\n    17→\n    18→    return Logger.getLogger(loggerName);\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  private String extractLoggerName(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n    22→    if (injectionPoint.getBean() == null) {\n    23→      return injectionPoint.getMember().getDeclaringClass().getName();\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    if (injectionPoint.getBean().getName() == null) {\n    27→      return injectionPoint.getBean().getBeanClass().getName();\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    return injectionPoint.getBean().getName();\n    31→  }\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SysReiXaKLo3SLnKUXjVfA","session_id":"c9dd45e7-15fd-4879-bcb7-e7ebc835a938","uuid":"24dd9b1d-7c22-4f01-bf8a-e2ab7c2a8a0b"}
